  "education": {
    "market_education": {
      "summary_en": "U.S. equities finished the final session of April near flat as investors digested month-end positioning and awaited upcoming economic data. The S&P 500 ended unchanged while the NASDAQ slipped 0.4%, with semiconductor and large-cap tech seeing mild profit-taking after a strong April recovery. Market breadth remained mixed, reflecting a tug-of-war between improving corporate earnings and lingering macro uncertainty around trade policy and Fed rate-cut timing.",
